Definition: with sincerity
Example: without pretense; she praised him sincerely for his victory; was unfeignedly glad to see his old teacher; we are truly sorry for the inconvenience
Synonyms: insincerely, adj, all, sincere, unfeignedly, unfeigned, truly, true, with, sincerity, without, pretense, she, praised, him, for, his, victory, was, glad, to, see, old, teacher, we, are, sorry, the, inconvenience
Category: adv.all
